results.name: Number of ways to write n as n = x*y*z with 1<x<=y<=z<n.
comment: x,y,z are proper factors of n. a(n) > 0 iff n is a term of A033942; a(n) = 0 iff n is a term of A037143.
link: Seiichi Manyama, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..8192 (terms 1..2048 from Antti Karttunen)
example: a(24) = 2 because 24 = 2*2*6 = 2*3*4, two products of three proper factors of 24.
program: (PARI) for(n=1,105, t=0; for(x=2,n-1, for(y=x,n-1, for(z=y,n-1, if(x*y*z==n, t++)))); print1(t,", "))
(PARI) A122179(n) = { my(s=0); fordiv(n, x, if((x>1)&&(x<n),for(y=x, n-1, for(z=y, n-1, if(x*y*z==n, s++))))); (s); }; \\ _Antti Karttunen_, Aug 24 2017
